    dc:description "FIG. 11. — Groutiella tomentosa (Hornsch.) Wijk & Margad.: A, plant; B-G, leaves; H, apical leaf cells; I, median marginal leaf cells; J, basal leaf cells; K, perichaetial bract; L, capsule; M, calyptra; N, portion of peristome; O, phaneropore; P, spores. A, K-P from Larsen et al. 2362 (MO); B, C from de Robillard s.n., lectotype of G. laxotorquata (Müll. Hal. ex Besch.) Wijk & Margad.; D-G from Allen 25041 (MO); H-J from Sellow s.n., lectotype of G. tomentosa, H. Scale bar: A, 1.2 cm; B-J, 90 µm; K, 0.9 mm; L, M, 3 mm; N-P, 130 µm. Credits: Yu N.-N. & Guo M. S." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8155713/files/figure.png" ;
